rComments: Absolutely love his teaching style. Unfortunately lectures are not recorded but material is clearly conveyed and assessment is relatively fair. So long as you take notes, you will be fine; definitely the best online format I have experienced to date.

Great lectures, exams are fair.
He knows his stuff and comes up with tons of daily examples to help students understand.
Wish the course was in person.
Best prof of the faculty!!!

This man is a gem of a professor, not only is he amazing at explaining concepts, he is also extremely caring and nice to students. His class wasn't easy by any means but he puts you on the right track by providing a nice amount of practice problems so if you want to get a good grade, you put the work in and you will get that grade!
Best prof of the faculty

Jodoin is one of the best profs I've ever had, he's hilarious and both understands his subject and how to teach it. He doesn't use anything online, but he'll distribute plenty of diagrams to explain the concepts. His passion is really teaching and it shows.

I'm not exaggerating when I say this is the best prof I've ever had in my entire life. Midterm and quizzes were fair and if it wasn't for Hallet's final exam being quite a bit tougher he would have a 5 so don't let those other comments saying "tough exams" suade you cause you won't avoid the final either way. Only downside is there's no brightspace

Outstanding teacher. I highly recommend that you take his Gas Dynamics as a 4th year elective, it's a very interesting topic and not outrageously challenging.

Super nice guy. He really knows his subject and how to teach it. His quizzes make sure that you know the material. Midterm and final were very straightforward.  Links everything together well by using graphs, images, videos, etc...  He made gas dynamics easy and fun!
By far the best teacher of the faculty.

Weekly quizzes ensure that you are keeping up with the class. If you work on the suggested problems before each quiz you will do great. Makes classes extremely interesting by giving actual engineering applications for the theory (learnt about the SR71 Blackbird, the Space Shuttle, etc). Overall, great guy, great prof.
Phenomenal teacher. Super interesting to listen to and pretty funny too. Makes class fun. Final is hard tho so watch out
